22/05/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- About 500 Macedonians were prevented from leaving the country due to lack of sound reasons for their stay in the EU, the Interior Ministry announced at a press conference on Friday (May 20th).
The figures refer to the period April 29th to May 19th.
The government have increased checks of the border crossing and the tourist agencies.
The authorities have stepped up the control amid speculations that Macedonia and Serbia could see their visa liberalisation regime suspended because of abuses.
(Kanal 5, Sitel, Makfax, Alsat M - 20/05/11)
